![Burning190.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1628699602433-2RN5YYV3973QPBHLQHNM/Burning190.jpg)

Task Force X is back! The group of expendable villains who are DYING to save the world have returned but with a new coat of paint courtesy of Guardians of The Galaxy director James Gunn. Gone are the neon and grunge of 2016 and instead we get more than a bit of blood and gore in this R Rated take on the doomed team. Join us as we discuss the highs and lows of the film and decide which we prefer more in this deep dive and spoiler-filled review of The Suicide Squad!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
